comment.narrative:
1) Some identified gaps now narrowed down in Viet Nam: (i) regulations on controlling corruption/bribery in the private sector; (ii) regulations on controlling corruption involving foreign public officials;
2) 3 policy research papers commissioned and 3 high-level policy dialogues convened together with the Central Commission on Internal Affairs (which is under the Vietnam Communist Party Central Committee, and advisory body for the Politburo in anti-corruption) on three topics: (i) Enhancing Mechanisms in Handling Corruption Crimes and in Law Enforcement; ii) Improving Provisions in the Criminal Procedural Code to Effectively Detect and Handle Corruption Crimes in Viet Nam; and (iii) Ways Forward to Enhanced Enforcement of the Anti-corruption Law in Viet Nam; 
3) 3-very significant. UNDP’s recommendations on how to address gaps in prevention, investigation and prosecution of corruption were incorporated into the 2015 Amendment to the Penal Code (especially in liability of legal entities though not yet in corruption crime due to Viet Nam's reservation, in corruption in the private sector, and in bribing foreign public officials). In addition, findings from an evidence-based research on corruption in the public sector in Viet Nam using PAPI data used in the Government Inspectorate's report to the National Assembly, creating significant public interest.

description.narrative:
1. Changes in major wetlands-related policies, laws  plans 
2. Capacity of MONRE to implement wetlands-related policies, legislation, strategies and programmes as measured by the Capacity Development Scorecard;
3. Availability of monetary and non-monetary valuation of ecosystem services, contributing to strengthening biodiversity conservation

comment.narrative:
1. Three changes observed in major wetlands-related policies, laws and plans, including: - An updated wetland classification system developed and finalized after consultation;
- An inventory data of Vietnam wetlands and detailed list of important wetlands developed and mapped;
- A proposal of a new decree on wetland conservation and sustainable use being developed and finalized after consultation;
2. Capacity building programme developed: 
- Training program and materials for strengthening wetland management capacity at central level developed and piloted, finalized after consultation;
- CIP office fully equiped for operation and ready for the training series;
- A proposal for National Wetland Working Group and Local Wetland Working Group establishment and operation developed and finalized after consultation;
3. Preparation for the development of monetary and non-monetary valuation of ecosystem services completed, including economic valuation report and communications documents
